                <h2>
                    1.	PURPOSE  &nbsp; :
                </h2>
                <p style="margin-left:30px;">
                    The purpose of this procedure is to describe the method for ensuring that the product that does not conform to
                    specified requirement is identified and controlled to prevent form unintended use or delivery. This control shall
                    provide for identification, documentation, evaluation, segregation and disposition of non-conforming product and
                    for notification to the functions concerned.
                </p>

                <h2>
                    2.	SCOPE  &nbsp; :
                </h2>
                <p style="margin-left:30px;">Applicable to all non-conforming products. </p>
                <h2>3.	RESPONSIBILITY &nbsp;&nbsp;:  </h2>

                <p style="margin-left:30px;">
                    QC supervisor, Production Supervisor, store incharge and Purchase officer is responsible to implement & maintain this procedure in their respective area.
                    PARTNER &nbsp;has an authority for final decision and disposition of non-conforming material.

                </p>

                <h2>

                    4.	PROCEDURE  &nbsp; :
                </h2>
                <p style="margin-left:30px;">
                    Non-conforming product means, which is not as per the specified requirement.
                </p>
                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">
                    4.1  NON-CONFORMING &nbsp; &nbsp; PRODUCT :
                </h3>
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    Non-conforming product observed at any stages, like during receiving inspection, in-process inspection and final
                    inspection are handled by one of the following ways.
                </p>

                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">
                    4.2	RECEIVING STAGE &nbsp;:
                </h3>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">4.2.1	RAW &nbsp; MATERIAL &nbsp;&nbsp; INSPECTION &nbsp;&nbsp;& TESTING :</h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">  RM shall be divided into OK, Rejection and Segregation or accepted under deviation.  </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">a)	REJECTION &nbsp;:</h5><br />
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">	Incase of rejection, QC &nbsp; Supervisor shall identify the rejected material as per process chart, doc. No. PCQC01 and send it to rejected area. QC &nbsp;Supervisor shall inform to purchase officer. Purchase officer shall send back the rejected material to concerned supplier and informed to him for necessary corrective action.</p>

                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">4.2.2	SUPPLIER’S &nbsp;&nbsp; SUPPLIED &nbsp;&nbsp;PRODUCT &nbsp;&nbsp;(CRITICAL &nbsp;&nbsp; ITEMS &nbsp;)</h5>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;"> a) REJECTION &nbsp; :</h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">In case of items found rejected, store incharge shall identify it and keeps at rejected area. Store incharge shall inform to concerned supplier. </p>

                <h3 style="margin-left:50px;">4.3	INPROCESS INSPECTION :</h3>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">a)	REWORK &nbsp; :</h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    In case of material found rework, the same shall be kept a side by identifying the reason for rework. At the end of the day, the same shall be reworked.
                </p>

