                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">

                    b)	REJECTION &nbsp;:
                </h5>

                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    In case of material found rejected, the same shall be recorded in setup approval & inprocess inspection report form no FQC02 at the end of day or shift. Rejected shall be identified and kept at rejection area.
                </p>
                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">4.4	FINAL INSPECTION : </h3><br />
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    The non-conformities observed during final inspection is divided into rework, rejection and accepted under deviation.
                </p>





                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    a)	REWORK &nbsp; :
                </h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    Incase of needing rework, QC &nbsp; supervisor shall keep them in a rework area and identify with a flag of “ REWORK“.
                    After doing rework, the same shall be re-inspected; QC &nbsp;supervisor shall keep the record in final inspection report,
                    form no. FQC03.

                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">

                    b)	REJECTION &nbsp;:
                </h5>

                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    Incase of rejected, the same shall be identified by red color & kept at rejected area. QC supervisor shall keep the
                    record of the same in final inspection report (critical parameters), form no. FQC03.
                </p>

                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;"> 4.5	ACCEPTED &nbsp; UNDER &nbsp; DEVIATION :</h3>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5.1
                </h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    Incase of material can be used with or without repair by concession; originator department shall inform and hand
                    over to PARTNER.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5.2
                </h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    PARTNER shall verify the same and gets approval from sales. PARTNER &nbsp; shall review the nature of fault and purpose of
                    the product and approve the same.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5.3
                </h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    After getting concession, the same material shall be properly identified and used for further process.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5.4
                </h5>

                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    Whenever required by the contract, the proposed use or repair of product, which does not confirm to specified
                    requirements, PARTNER &nbsp; shall inform to marketing officer for getting approval from the customer. In that case,
                    material shall be identified properly and used for further process only after getting approval from the customer.
                </p>
                <h5 style="margin-left:50px;">
                    4.5.5
                </h5>
                <p style="margin-left:70px;">
                    Incase of customer does not give the deviation; PARTNER &nbsp; shall decide to send for alternative application.
                    In that case PARTNER &nbsp;shall inform to marketing officer to store the material with proper identification and
                    dispatched as per requirement.
                </p>

                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">
                    4.6	NONCONFORMING &nbsp; MATERIAL &nbsp;RETURNED &nbsp;FROM &nbsp; THE CUSTOMER :
                </h3>
                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    Incase of non-conforming material returned from the customer, QC &nbsp; supervisor shall analyze the same and follow the steps as given in para 4.5 or para 6. The results are recorded in corrective action report, form no. F MR 09.
                </p>

